CMPUT 275, Winter 2020

Weekly Exercise 2: Restaurants and Pointers

--------------
Included Files
--------------
    * get_restaurant.cpp
    * Makefile
    * README

-----------
Accessories
-----------
    * Arduino Mega 2560 Board X1
    * USB cable type A/B X1
    * 3.5" TFT LCD 480x320 HD color screen module for Arduino UNO & MEGA 2560
        board with touch panel X1

--------------------
Wiring Instructions
--------------------
    * Connect appropriate pins on the TFT display to the Arduino.

---------------------
Running Instructions
---------------------
    1. Connect the Arduino with the appropriate componenets (ex: TFT display) to
    a computer using an A-B style USB cable. Ensure that the Arduino is using
    the proper serial port (/dev/ttyACMO0).

    2. In the directory containing the files get_restaurant.cpp and Makefile,
    use the command "make upload" to upload the code to the Arduino.

----------------------
Notes and Assumptions
----------------------
    * The function runAvg() assumes that the run times do not overflow an
    unsigned long.
